overview: Contrasts the traffic court of the horse and buggy era with that of today. Emphasizes that it is the traffic court judge's responsibility to increase respect for judicial authority.

Why was he fired as General of the Third Army and relegated to a governorship of post-war Bavaria? Who were his enemies? Was he a threat to Eisenhower, Montgomery, Churchill, and Bradley? And is it possible as some say that the General's freakish collision with an Army truck, on the day before his departure for US, was not really an accident?
